# Field-test harness (Plan 35) — auth for the UNATTENDED, egress-fenced blind runs.
# Copy this file to `.env` in the SAME directory (scripts/field-test/.env) and fill
# in the key. `.env` is gitignored (repo-root `.gitignore` ignores `.env` at any
# depth) — never commit it.
#
# The nested blind `claude` runs inside a Docker container whose ONLY network
# egress is api.anthropic.com (an allowlist-proxy sidecar). This key is the ONLY
# credential that crosses into the container (via `docker run -e ANTHROPIC_API_KEY`);
# nothing else from your shell env is passed in. Use a key with a LOW spend cap —
# an unattended round must never be able to burn your quota.
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=

# --- optional overrides (uncomment to change a default) ---
# FIELD_MODEL=sonnet          # blind-agent model — Sonnet is the fixed cast (Plan 35)
# FIELD_RUN_BUDGET_MIN=60     # total wall-clock kill for one unattended round (minutes)
# FIELD_N8N_TAG=              # n8n image tag (default: the smoke-suite pin)
